On 5 March 2020, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize announced the first case of coronavirus in South Africa. Here's how the situation has unfolded since then. On 5 March 2020, Health Minister Zweli Mkhize announced the first case of coronavirus in South Africa. By midday on 6 April 2020 - a month later - the country had 1,655 confirmed cases, 11 deaths and was in the midst of a 21-day lockdown. This is a timeline of the coronavirus pandemic in South Africa to date. 